A lot of emulators can take .nes.zip files. If you have a bank of all $FF bytes somewhere in PRG or CHR, it will compress down to nearly nothing and then decompress on load.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Apr 09, 2005 12:37 pm</p><hr />
