<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=271&amp;p=1806#p1806"><![CDATA[
Hum, I'm not sure that you got it.<br />Unless you're re-inventing a new mapper like I said above, you can't have ROM size that isn't 2^n, so this is **NOT** possible with MMC3. Just look at all games and demos out there, they all have a 2^n PRG chip and 2^n CHR chip. May some old stupid demoes of the same style as "junkdemo" does, but if any does this is just gabrage.<br />This is just a glich in the iNES header, they could decide to input "number of times you have to double the size of a 16kb PRG-ROM" instead of "number of 16kb PRG-ROM bank". Also, there is not always 16kb banks, but also 8kb or 32 kb from the various mappers. The smallest ROM possible is still 16kb.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Sat Apr 09, 2005 11:12 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
