Yeah, just watch the pinout of an EPROM. You have X pins of adress imput, adding one pin will double the size of the ROM, removing one pin will half it. You'll definitly need to have a 64kb PRG rom. The only way to have odd ROM size would be to combine two different ROM chip with two different sizes, I know that many SNES games does that.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Wed Apr 06, 2005 12:18 pm</p><hr />
