<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=271&amp;p=1774#p1774"><![CDATA[
All roms have a prg size of 2^n (32k, 64k, 128k, etc) so many emus use "0xFFFF &amp; (prg_banks - 1)" to refer to the last bank. I know I do, at least.<br />In your case, it would mean that the third bank is ignored and the second bank is used as if it were the last one.<p>Statistics: Posted by Guest — Wed Apr 06, 2005 10:43 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
